  "prompt": "How much refund will I get on my PRS counter ticket if my seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train? Can I board the train using it",
  "response": "According to Indian Railways refund policy:\n\n1. Full Refund Scenario:\n- If your waitlisted ticket remains unconfirmed even after the train's departure, you are eligible for a full refund\n- No deduction will be made for cancellation charges\n\n2. Refund Process:\n- You must submit the ticket at the reservation counter within 1 month of the train's scheduled departure\n- Refund will be processed through the original payment mode\n\n3. Boarding the Train:\n- With a waitlisted ticket that remains unconfirmed, you CANNOT board the train\n- You would need a confirmed seat/berth to travel\n\n4. Refund Mechanism:\n- Refund can be claimed at the reservation counter\n- Online refunds are also possible through IRCTC website\n- Refund is typically credited back to the original payment method within 7-10 working days\n\n5. Important Note:\n- Always check your ticket status before traveling\n- If the ticket remains waitlisted, do not proceed to the station\n\nTo get the exact refund, visit the nearest railway reservation counter with your original ticket for precise processing.",
